cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LM, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new logic with second-order quantifiers and studies its expressive power.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the limited nondeterminism class $\beta\text{P}$ and its relationship with the new logic.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper deals with ordered structures, which are a type of data structure.
- cs.LM (Learning) is a possibility as the paper introduces a new version of the Ehrenfeucht-Fraisse game, which is a tool used in learning theory.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possibility as the new logic and its expressive power may have implications for AI applications.
